overview: The user requested a scroll-to-top button for the website. The
  assistant began by exploring the codebase to understand the project structure,
  existing components, and styling conventions. It then created a new
  client-side React component named . This component
  dynamically appears after the user scrolls down 300 pixels and is fixed at the
  bottom-right of the viewport. Upon clicking, it smoothly scrolls the page back
  to the top. The button features an inline SVG up arrow and is styled using
  TailwindCSS to match the site's existing design system. Finally, the
   component was integrated into the  to ensure its
  presence across all pages, and linting was checked to confirm correctness.
